<!-- SECTION 1: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>

<div class="info"><strong>Content Quality:</strong> Match preview articles average 2,500–3,500 words, are well-researched, and deliver genuine value to World Cup 2026 fans. The editorial foundation is solid. However, technical implementation is critically deficient in four areas that prevent good content from being discovered.</div>

<div class="critical"><strong>SEO &amp; Social Sharing — Critical:</strong> 13 of 14 pages have zero meta descriptions, zero Open Graph tags, zero Twitter Card tags, and zero canonical tags simultaneously. Every social share on Facebook, Twitter/X, LinkedIn, or WhatsApp renders as a plain bare URL — no image, no title, no description. The site is actively suppressing its own traffic.</div>

<div class="warning"><strong>Mobile — Critical:</strong> Viewport meta tag missing/unconfirmed on most pages. No hamburger menu on 12 of 14 pages. A navbar with 35+ links and no collapse mechanism is completely unusable on smartphones — which is where the majority of sports fans browse.</div>

<div class="warning"><strong>Accessibility — Persistent WCAG Level A failures:</strong> Logo alt text missing on all 14 pages. 60%+ of content images lack alt text. All newsletter forms lack proper label elements. ARIA roles and attributes absent throughout.</div>

<div class="caution"><strong>Placeholder Content in Production:</strong> "Photo · TBC" captions on 4+ pages, "Form: TBC · verify" live in squad tables, "Awaiting FIFA confirmation" text published, and an entirely empty content section on the Mexico vs South Africa page.</div>

<!-- SECTION 2: SITE-WIDE CRITICAL ISSUES -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>2. Site-Wide Critical Issues</h2>
<p><em>These problems appear on every page — fixing them in one place fixes all 14 pages.</em></p>

<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Issue</th><th>Severity</th><th>Affects</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td><strong>No Open Graph Tags</strong> — og:title, og:description, og:image missing. Every social share = bare URL.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>13/14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td><strong>No Twitter Card Tags</strong> — Zero visual on X/Twitter shares.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>13/14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td><strong>No Meta Description</strong> — Google auto-generates bad SERP snippets.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>13/14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td><strong>No Canonical Tag</strong> — Duplicate content risk across URL variants.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>13/14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td><strong>Logo alt="" missing</strong> — WCAG 2.1 SC 1.1.1 Level A failure on every page.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6</td><td><strong>"Editorial Team" footer = href='#'</strong> — Dead placeholder link, clicks do nothing.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>7</td><td><strong>No Social Media Links in Footer</strong> — No Twitter/X, Instagram, Facebook, YouTube anywhere.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>8</td><td><strong>/wp-login.php in Public Navbar</strong> — Shows as "Sign in". Exposes WP login to bots.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>Multiple pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>9</td><td><strong>Newsletter Privacy Policy = href='#'</strong> — Consent link goes nowhere. GDPR risk.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>Multiple pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>10</td><td><strong>No JSON-LD Structured Data on any page</strong> — Ineligible for Google rich results.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>11</td><td><strong>No Hamburger Menu</strong> — 35+ nav links with zero mobile collapse. Nav broken on phones.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>12/14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>12</td><td><strong>Viewport Meta Tag Missing</strong> — Mobile browsers render desktop layout at 980px width.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td><td>Most pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>13</td><td><strong>"Photo · TBC" Live in Production</strong> — Incomplete placeholder visible to all users.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>4+ pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>14</td><td><strong>"All Stories" Footer → Homepage "/"</strong> — Misleading navigation label.</td><td><span class="badge-yellow">MEDIUM</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>15</td><td><strong>Related Article Card Images Missing Alt Text</strong> — Appear on 6+ pages without alt attributes.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">HIGH</span></td><td>6+ pages</td></tr>
</table>

