<!-- SECTION 4: FOOTER -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>4. Footer Analysis</h2>

<h3>What Works Correctly</h3>
<div class="ok">Copyright "© 2026 Fanorate. Published by Brillmark LLC" — year is correct for June 2026</div>
<div class="ok">Legal pages present: Privacy Policy, Terms of Use, Cookie Policy, Affiliate Disclosure, Our Methodology</div>
<div class="ok">Multi-column layout (Editorial / About / Trust) is clean and well-organized</div>

<h3>What Is Broken</h3>
<div class="critical">"Editorial Team" link → href='#' — Dead link on ALL 14 pages. Clicks go nowhere. Must be fixed or removed.</div>
<div class="critical">No social media links anywhere in the footer on any page — no Twitter/X, Instagram, Facebook, YouTube. Critical gap for a sports publication.</div>
<div class="warning">"All Stories" → points to "/" (homepage), not a stories archive. Misleading label for all visitors.</div>
<div class="warning">No GDPR/cookie consent banner despite Cookie Policy link existing. Potential EU compliance violation.</div>
<div class="caution">No RSS feed link — missed opportunity for feed subscribers on a news/editorial site.</div>

<!-- SECTION 5: FORMS -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>5. Forms Analysis</h2>

<h3>Newsletter Signup (Contact Form 7 — all pages)</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Check</th><th>Status</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Form present</td><td><span class="pass">✓ All pages</span></td><td>Newsletter email form present sitewide</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Email input label</td><td><span class="fail">✗ MISSING</span></td><td>No &lt;label&gt; element on any page. Uses placeholder text only — WCAG SC 1.3.1 failure</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Submit button</td><td><span class="pass">✓ Present</span></td><td>Submit button exists but label text unconfirmed on most pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Privacy policy link</td><td><span class="fail">✗ BROKEN</span></td><td>Links to href='#' on multiple pages — GDPR compliance risk. Must point to /privacy-policy/</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Form action URL</td><td><span class="warn">⚠ Unconfirmed</span></td><td>Could not confirm on most pages where submissions are sent</td></tr>
  <tr><td>CAPTCHA / bot protection</td><td><span class="fail">✗ Missing</span></td><td>No spam protection mechanism detected on any page</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Success/error states</td><td><span class="warn">⚠ Unconfirmed</span></td><td>No validation feedback confirmed on any page</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Site Search Form</h3>
<div class="caution">The "US · EN" element in the header has ambiguous UX — unclear if it functions as a search bar, a locale switcher, or both. Only the Mexico vs South Africa page confirms aria-label="Search" on the input. All other pages unconfirmed.</div>

<h3>WordPress Login Link ("Sign in")</h3>
<div class="critical">The /wp-login.php link in the public navbar is not a form but functions as a login entry point. Remove from public navigation immediately — it exposes the CMS platform to attackers and regular readers cannot log into WordPress admin.</div>

<!-- SECTION 6: MOBILE -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>6. Mobile Responsiveness</h2>

<table>
  <tr><th>Mobile Check</th><th>Status</th><th>Pages Affected</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Viewport meta tag</td><td><span class="fail">✗ Missing/unconfirmed</span></td><td>~10 of 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mobile hamburger menu</td><td><span class="fail">✗ Missing</span></td><td>12 of 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Images with loading="lazy"</td><td><span class="fail">✗ Not detected</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Images with srcset (responsive)</td><td><span class="fail">✗ Not confirmed</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Data tables responsive</td><td><span class="warn">⚠ Not confirmed</span></td><td>Head-to-Head + lineup tables</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Image format (WebP)</td><td><span class="warn">⚠ All .png only</span></td><td>All 14 pages (25–35% size saving missed)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Touch target sizes (44×44px)</td><td><span class="warn">⚠ Not verified</span></td><td>All 14 pages</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="critical"><strong>Critical Mobile Impact:</strong> Without a viewport meta tag, every mobile browser renders the page at ~980px wide — users must pinch-zoom to read anything. Without a hamburger menu, a 35-link navbar physically overflows the screen on a phone. Sports content is consumed predominantly on mobile — this is the primary audience being failed.</div>

<div class="caution"><strong>Performance Note:</strong> The Mexico vs South Africa page loads 27 separate CSS files as render-blocking resources. All pages serve PNG images without lazy loading or srcset. WordPress caching plugin and CDN configuration should be verified before World Cup traffic peaks.</div>

