<div class="warning"><strong>Yoast SEO Note (Mexico page):</strong> The theme independently emits a second &lt;title&gt; tag alongside Yoast, producing invalid HTML. Yoast reports wordCount as 6 for a 3,200-word article — all content is in Gutenberg blocks not being counted. Twitter card shows "1 minute" read time; actual is 13 minutes. Configure Yoast globally across all pages to resolve the 12-page gap in one pass.</div>

<!-- SECTION 8: ACCESSIBILITY -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>8. Accessibility Analysis (WCAG 2.1)</h2>

<table>
  <tr><th>WCAG Criterion</th><th>Level</th><th>Status</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1.1.1 Non-text Content — Logo alt</td><td><span class="badge-red">A</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL × 14</span></td><td>Logo img missing alt attribute on every page</td></tr>
  <tr><td>1.1.1 Non-text Content — Images</td><td><span class="badge-red">A</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL</span></td><td>60%+ of content images missing alt text. Germany (6/6), Qatar (4/5), Australia (3/4)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>1.3.1 Info &amp; Relationships — Forms</td><td><span class="badge-red">A</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL × 14</span></td><td>Newsletter email input has no &lt;label&gt; element on any page</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2.4.1 Bypass Blocks — Skip link</td><td><span class="badge-red">A</span></td><td><span class="pass">PASS</span></td><td>#wp--skip-link--target present on all WordPress pages ✅</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2.4.2 Page Titled</td><td><span class="badge-red">A</span></td><td><span class="pass">PASS</span></td><td>Title tags present on all pages ✅</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3.1.1 Language of Page</td><td><span class="badge-red">A</span></td><td><span class="warn">⚠ UNCONFIRMED</span></td><td>lang="en" on &lt;html&gt; not confirmed — screen readers need this attribute</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4.1.2 Name, Role, Value — Nav</td><td><span class="badge-orange">AA</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL</span></td><td>Nav dropdowns missing aria-expanded, aria-haspopup, aria-controls on most pages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4.1.2 — Hamburger button</td><td><span class="badge-orange">AA</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL</span></td><td>Mobile toggle not confirmed to have aria-label or aria-expanded</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2.5.5 Target Size — Touch</td><td><span class="badge-orange">AA</span></td><td><span class="warn">⚠ UNVERIFIED</span></td><td>Minimum 44×44px not confirmed for nav links and buttons</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Lineup pitch accessible alt</td><td><span class="badge-orange">AA</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL</span></td><td>Mexico page: pitch is aria-hidden with no text alternative. Screen readers get zero info.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>FAQ accordion ARIA</td><td><span class="badge-orange">AA</span></td><td><span class="fail">FAIL</span></td><td>FAQ items lack role="button", aria-expanded, aria-controls on multiple pages</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- SECTION 9: CONTENT QUALITY -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h2>9. Content Quality Analysis</h2>
<p><em>Based on detailed editorial review of 4 key pages (Mexico vs South Africa, USA vs Paraguay, Netherlands vs Japan, Ivory Coast vs Ecuador) plus structural analysis of all 14 pages.</em></p>

<div class="info"><strong>Overall:</strong> The writing quality is genuinely good. Articles are well-crafted, fan-focused, and topically rich. The voice is consistent — authoritative yet accessible, written for engaged football fans. Sections like "Five Storylines", "Key Players", "Squad Breakdown", and "Bold Prediction" follow a strong, engaging template. However, several pages contain factual errors and placeholder text that undermine credibility.</div>

<h3>Content Quality Scores (Reviewed Pages)</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Page</th><th>Content Score</th><th>Summary</th></tr>
  <tr><td>USA vs Paraguay</td><td>7.5 / 10</td><td>Strongest narrative drive, best tactical depth, excellent closing paragraph. Minor formatting artifact in "Secondary Angles" section.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mexico vs South Africa</td><td>7.0 / 10</td><td>Best atmosphere writing, strong opener. Questionable factual claim about South Africa's World Cup record. Empty historical facts section.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ivory Coast vs Ecuador</td><td>7.0 / 10</td><td>Strong Ecuador characterisation. Two factual errors (Singo's position, Ecuador's 2022 tournament description).</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Netherlands vs Japan</td><td>6.5 / 10</td><td>Flattest writing, broken lineup section (jersey numbers only — no player names). Five Storylines underdeveloped.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>What Works Well</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Consistent, engaging article template across all previews (Fixture → Storylines → Squad → Key Players → Lineups → Prediction → FAQ)</li>
  <li>Writing is fan-oriented and reads like genuine sports journalism — not AI-generic filler</li>
  <li>Match statistics and historical context are well-researched and specific</li>
  <li>FAQ sections target real fan questions ("When does it kick off?", "How to watch?", "Who are the key players?")</li>
  <li>Word counts are strong (2,500–3,500 words) — appropriate depth for SEO and reader value</li>
  <li>Bold prediction sections are specific and memorable, not vague hedging</li>
  <li>Breadcrumb navigation present and correct on most pages</li>
</ul>

<h3>Content Issues Found</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Page</th><th>Issue</th><th>Type</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Netherlands vs Japan</td><td>Only ~220 words — all other pages are 2,500–3,500 words. No images. Not production-ready.</td><td><span class="badge-red">CRITICAL</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Netherlands vs Japan</td><td>Predicted lineup shows only jersey numbers (1 2 3 4 5 6 8 14 10 9 7) — player names never filled in. Template artifact.</td><td><span class="badge-red">Bug</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ivory Coast vs Ecuador</td><td>Sangaré listed twice in lineup (as GK and as midfielder). Factual error.</td><td><span class="badge-red">Factual</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ivory Coast vs Ecuador</td><td>Nicolas Pépé listed as key winger despite retiring from international football.</td><td><span class="badge-red">Factual</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ivory Coast vs Ecuador</td><td>Wilfried Singo described as "center-back" — he is a fullback/right-back. Positional error.</td><td><span class="badge-red">Factual</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ivory Coast vs Ecuador</td><td>"Ecuador narrowly missed Round of 16 in 2022" — factually wrong. Ecuador finished 3rd in group and were eliminated.</td><td><span class="badge-red">Factual</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mexico vs South Africa</td><td>"Bafana Bafana haven't won a World Cup match since 1998" — suspect, given 2010 home tournament. Needs verification.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Factual Check</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mexico vs South Africa</td><td>Empty "Fun Historical Facts" section — heading present, zero content items. Visually broken.</td><td><span class="badge-red">Bug</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mexico vs South Africa</td><td>Duplicate pull quote: "If you only watch one match this week, this is the one." appears twice consecutively.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Error</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>USA vs Paraguay</td><td>"Secondary Angles" section contains raw unformatted probability fragments ("USA clean sheet: Moderate", "Margin (median): +1") — unedited template data left in article.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Template</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Canada vs Bosnia Herzegovina</td><td>"Awaiting FIFA confirmation" text published live in the article.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Placeholder</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Brazil vs Morocco</td><td>"Form: TBC · verify" in squad comparison tables — published with unfilled data fields.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Placeholder</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Qatar vs Switzerland</td><td>"Photo · TBC" caption live on featured image.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Placeholder</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sweden vs Tunisia</td><td>"Photo · TBC" caption live on featured stadium image.</td><td><span class="badge-orange">Placeholder</span></td></tr>
